\section{Étale sheafification}

Iteration~008 lands the étale-sheafified relative Picard functor on top of $\PicardFunctorAb$. The Mathlib gap that previously blocked this (\lstinline{HasSheafify} for the étale topology over $\Spec k$ valued in $\AddCommGrpCat$) closed in current Mathlib (iter-007 plan-agent re-probe). The only remaining gymnastic is universe-pinning: the inferable \lstinline{HasSheafify} is at value-universe $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u{+}1\}$, while the iter-004 $\PicardFunctorAb$ lands at $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\}$; we bridge the gap by post-composing with $\AddCommGrpCat.\mathtt{uliftFunctor}$.

\begin{definition}[Étale-sheafified relative Picard functor]
  \label{def:PicardFunctorAb_etaleSheafified}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.PicardFunctorAb.etaleSheafified}
  \uses{def:Pic_functorAb}
  Let $C$ be a scheme over $\Spec k$. The \emph{étale-sheafified relative Picard functor} of $C$ over $k$ is the étale sheaf on $\Sch_k$ obtained by sheafifying $\PicardFunctorAb\, C$ post-composed with the natural universe lift $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u\} \to \AddCommGrpCat.\{u{+}1\}$:
  \[
    \PicardFunctorAb.\mathrm{etaleSheafified}\, C \;\colon\;
    \mathtt{Sheaf}\bigl(((\mathtt{Scheme.etaleTopology.}\{u\}).\mathtt{over}\,(\Spec\,(\mathtt{CommRingCat.of}\,k)))\,,\,\AddCommGrpCat.\{u{+}1\}\bigr).
  \]
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:Pic_functorAb}
  Apply \lstinline{CategoryTheory.presheafToSheaf} (the Mathlib left-adjoint of the forgetful functor $\Sheaf \to \Pre$) to the universe-lifted presheaf. The probe-confirmed closure body is
  \begin{lstlisting}
  (CategoryTheory.presheafToSheaf _ _).obj
    (PicardFunctorAb C ⋙ AddCommGrpCat.uliftFunctor.{u+1, u}).
  \end{lstlisting}
  The two \lstinline{HasWeakSheafify} / \lstinline{HasSheafify} instances are now inferable in current Mathlib for the étale topology over $\Spec k$ valued in $\AddCommGrpCat.\{u{+}1\}$, so \lstinline{presheafToSheaf} types out without extra hypotheses.
\end{proof}

\section{Use in the project}

Definitions~\ref{def:Pic_functorAb} and~\ref{def:PicardFunctorAb_etaleSheafified} set up the codomain needed for:

\begin{itemize}
  \item The étale-sheafified version of the relative Picard functor of Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_Functor}: the input shape required by Grothendieck's representability machinery (FGA / Hilbert / Quot schemes) is a sheaf for the étale topology, not a presheaf. Definition~\ref{def:PicardFunctorAb_etaleSheafified} produces such a sheaf.
  \item Comparison with the Jacobian's $\Pic^0$ as a group scheme: the connected-component-of-identity of the representing scheme is a group object in $\Sch_k$; identifying $\PicardFunctorAb \cong \mathrm{HomFunctor}(\Pic_{C/k})$ via Yoneda is the cleanest path to the four \lstinline{Jacobian.lean} sorries.
  \item Direct definition of $H^n$-of-the-Picard-presheaf if a future iteration wants to expose it as a derived functor.
\end{itemize}

The representability theorem \ref{thm:Pic_representable} of Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_Functor} carries over verbatim once the étale sheafification of $\PicardFunctorAb$ has been constructed (Phase~C step~3, landed in iter-008); the four \lstinline{Jacobian.lean} sorries are the same as before, and the remaining gating obstruction for representability is the $\LineBundle$ refinement of Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle} (still blocked on absent $\MonoidalCategory$ on $X.\mathrm{Modules}$). This chapter does \emph{not} add a representability theorem of its own — the present chapter is the codomain change plus the étale sheafification.

